IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Crash Team Investigation (For review by the MSP Crash Team) NARRATIVE: On March 10, 2023 at approximately 1430 hours, the Federalsburg Police Department responded to the area of Route 313 and Preston Road located in Caroline County, Maryland, for a report of a serious motor vehicle collision. The collision involved a Tractor Trailer and a passenger car and both vehicles only had a single occupant. The driver of the passenger car was declared deceased on scene by Caroline Emergency Medical Services and the driver of the tractor trailer did not require medical attention. Federalsburg Police Department requested the assistance of MSP Crash Team for reconstructing the crash. A report documenting my activities will be completed and attached to RMS. ATTACHED SUPPORTING DOCUMENTATION: The following items were attached to this report: text-align: left;">None The following digital photographs were taken as part of this investigation and placed into Veri-Pic: text-align: left;">None The following items have been archived in the Crash Team Files: None INVESTIGATION STATUS: A report will be authored to document my activities as part of the investigation. This case is open. Authored by: Trooper First Class Christopher Bekefi #7098 MSP Easton Barrack 7053 Ocean Gateway Easton, MD 21601 410-822-3101 text-decoration:underline">Christopher.bekefi@maryland.gov

Detailed Crash Investigation Report (For review by the MSPCrash Team) Section I. - Introduction: On March 10, 2023, at approximately 1430 hours, Federalsburg Police Departments responded to the intersection of Rt. 313 and Preston Rd located in Federalsburg, Caroline County, Maryland for a two-vehicle motor vehicle collision involving a commercial vehicle tractor-trailer and a passenger car. Upon Sgt. Jacksons arrival, he learned that the motor vehicle collision involved the listed vehicles and persons. Vehicle #1: 2015 White ford Fusion, MD 5FC5271 Registered Owner: Williamson, Betty Anne Driver: MD Williamson, Betty Anne (11/12/1948, 2/F) (Deceased) Vehicle #2 2005 Red Freightliner Truck Tractor, IN 3249484 Registered Owner: TRX Inc. Driver: PA Torres, Julian (03/19/1966, 5/M) Upon Federalsburg PD and EMS arrival on scene, they had declared that Williamson was deceased on scene at 1438 hours by Paramedic 11 EMS run number 8636. Torres was evaluated by EMS but ultimately refused medical treatment.Federalsburg PD then contacted the MSP Easton Barrack to request MSP Crash Team respond to the scene and conduct a collision reconstruction. Sgt. Gore #5555 assigned to Crash Team and myself responded for the reconstruction and arrived at approximately 1525 hours. The MSP Commercial Vehicle Division was contacted and TFC G. Lapinski #6286 responded to the scene to conduct a post-crash inspection on the commercial motor vehicle. Upon my arrival, I made contact with Sgt. Jackson from Federalsburg PD on scene and he stated the tractor-trailer was traveling south on Maryland Route 313 through the Preston Road intersection. The Ford Fusion was traveling east on Preston Road and was attempting to go through the intersection into Federalsburg. The roadway was dry and the weather was cloudy. I made contact with Torres who advised me that he had the green light and the Fusion began to accelerate through the intersection as he reached the intersection. Torres also advised me that he had dash camera footage from his truck that he provided to me. I then proceeded to review the scene and upon completion began taking digital photographs of marked roadway evidence and the vehicles involved to document the scene. The tractor-trailer had significant front-end damage starting approximately at the top of the grill and extending down to the bottom of the front bumper. The Fusion was located off the northbound side of Route 313 in a grassy area. The Fusion had heavy damage to the driver side of the vehicle extending from the front wheel back to the rear panel. The windshield had been shattered from the impact of the collision and there was tire rubber transfer on the rear panel of the fusion. Section II. - Scene Description: (The following descriptions are based on the area where the collision occurred.) Primary Roadway:Maryland Route 313 (Federalsburg Highway) Maryland Route 313 known as Federalsburg Highway is an undivided highway that travels in a north and south direction. The roadway has one lane of travel in each direction. The travel lanes are separated by a double yellow line painted on the roadway surface. The travel lanes are supported by a small shoulder and are separated by solid white lines on roadway surface. The below photograph is facing the southbound direction approaching the Preston Road / Bloomingdale Avenue Intersection and the point of view Torres had prior to the collision. The southbound side of Maryland Rt. 313 consisted of a left turn lane to travel east onto Bloomingdale Ave. a center lane to continue south on Maryland Rt. 313, and a right turn lane to travel west on Preston Road (Rt. 318). Torres was attempting to continue southbound on Maryland Rt. 313 with the right away at the four way traffic signal. The speed limit on Maryland Rt. 313 is 50 miles per hour. base64," style="height:326px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> The above image was captured from Google Maps which accurately depicts the southbound side of MD Rt. 313 as described above. Secondary Roadway (if applicable): Maryland Rt. 318 (Preston Road) Maryland Rt. 318 also known as Preston Road is an undivided highway that travels in an east and west direction with one lane of travel for each direction. Maryland Rt. 318 intersects with Federalsburg Hwy prior to becoming Maryland Route 315, Bloomingdale Ave., east of the intersection. The below photograph is facing the eastbound direction at the traffic signal where Williamson was stopped at the red signal in the center lane of travel. The speed limit on Maryland Rt. 318 is 50 mph. base64," style="height:321px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> The above image captured from Google Maps, which accurately depicts the eastbound side of MD Rt. 318 as described above. The roadway was constructed with paved asphalt material and appeared to be in good condition with no defects. The roadway markings were clear and the roadway surface was dry at the time of crash. base64," style="height:386px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> The above image captured from the MDOT SHA Speed limit map, which accurately depicts the posted speed limit on Maryland Route 313. Traffic Control Devices: There is a traffic control device present at the intersection of Maryland Route 313 and Maryland Route 318. While I was on scene, I observed the traffic signal cycle multiple times and appeared to be operating and functioning properly. According to the Maryland Department of Transportation Traffic Operations Support Section, there were no reports of any malfunctions on March 10, 2023.The traffic signal at the intersection of Maryland Route 313 and Maryland Route 318 was responsive, which means that the time given to each phase varies based on the present traffic conditions. The Maryland Department of Transportation State Highway Administration Traffic Operations Support provided the most current information concerning the timing and phasing data for the intersection, which is attached to this Detailed Crash Investigation Report. Environmental Conditions: The environmental conditions at the time of crash were of the following. margin-left:8px"> Surface Air Temperature- Approximately 54 degrees Fahrenheit margin-left:8px"> Cloud Cover- Cloudy margin-left:8px"> Wind conditions- 10 mph from the South margin-left:8px"> Precipitation- 0 inches margin-left:8px"> Sunrise/Sunset- 0623/1805 hours Obtained information from www.Weatherunderground.com The collision occurred during daylight hours, therefore, no artificial lighting conditions were observed. Section III. - Scene Evidence: margin-left:8px"> I began documenting the scene from north of the Federalsburg Bypass/ Preston Road intersection where the collision occurred. As I walked south towards the collision, I did not locate any pre-impact tire markings. I then located post impact tire marks that were located in the intersection of Federalsburg Bypass and Preston Road. I determined all tire marks to belong solely to the Tractor Trailer. I located a scrape mark that was on the driver side tire marks of the tractor-trailer. The tractor-trailer had come to an areaof final rest in the middle of the intersection on the northbound lane of Route 313. The truck tractor had heavy front-end damage from where it struck the Ford Fusion. margin-left:8px"> I located a single tirerut where the Ford Fusion had entered the grass off the roadway. Tire marks were located leading up to where the Ford Fusion had come to a position of final rest. There were no markings in the intersection that would indicate the Ford Fusion attempted to take evasive action to avoid the impact with the Tractor Trailer. Section IV. - Vehicle(s) Involved: Vehicle #1: margin-left:8px"> 2015 White Ford Fusion MD 5FC5271 margin-left:8px"> VIN- 3FA6P0H73FR190706 margin-left:8px"> Registered Owner-Betty Anne Williamson 3451 Houston Branch Rd Federalsburg, MD 21632 The Ford was found approximately 25 feet off the northbound shoulder of Maryland Route 313 facing in a south-east direction. The main impact to the Ford occurred on the driver side front end to the driver door and sustained severe damage when the Freightliner struck the vehicle. The driver side damage from the front end to the driver portion intruded to the interior of the vehicle. The front driver side wheel had been bent from the axle and was resting at an approximate 45-degree angle to the ground. The main contact caused the front bumper to detach from the vehicle and the hood to fold in a V shape (See Image 1877). The Ford sustained minor damage from the rear driver side door back to the rear of the vehicle. The main contact caused the rear door to sustain a wrinkling affect and become unlatched from the closed position. The rear panel was moved from position and also had black tire scuffing from the Truck. margin-left:8px">An interior inspection shows that there was severe interior intrusion to the vehicle. The front and side curtain airbags were commanded to deploy on impact. The deceased was still seated in driver seat of the vehicle upon inspection. base64," style="height:466px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> The above photograph IMG 1887 is an accurate depiction of the damage sustained at impact of the crash. The front bumper of the Freightliner was also detached from the vehicle. No damages were sustained to the Trailer. An interior inspection shows no airbags were commanded to deploy, and no damages sustained to the interior of the Freightliner from the collision event. base64," style="height:466px; margin:5px 10px; width:700px" /> The above photograph IMG 1859 is an accurate depiction of the damage sustained at impact of the crash. Caroline County EMS Paramedic 11 EMS Run number 8636 declared Williamson deceased on scene at 1438 hours. Forensic Investigator Bart Cohey responded to the scene and Framptons Funeral Home transported Williamson to the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME) located in Baltimore, MD for an autopsy. margin-left:8px"> Impairment- None Detected. margin-left:8px"> Next of Kin- Notification made to husband William Luther Williamson by Federalsburg PD. margin-left:8px"> Valid Class C Maryland Drivers License Person #2: Driver of Freightliner margin-left:8px"> Julian Torres margin-left:8px"> DOB- 03/19/1966, 5/M margin-left:8px"> OLN- PA 28392016 Residence- 1202 Gilham St Philadelphia, PA 19111 margin-left:8px"> Injury Severity- Refused treatment from EMS on scene. margin-left:8px"> Impairment- None Detected margin-left:8px"> Valid Class A Pennsylvania Drivers License Section VI. - Follow-up Investigation: margin-left:8px"> On Friday April 28, 2023,I emailed the Maryland Department of Transportation (MDOT) State Highway Administration (SHA) requesting a copy of timing chart data, a phasing diagram, and any reports of malfunctions to the traffic signal for the intersection. margin-left:8px"> On Tuesday May 9, 2023, I received a response to my request from the MDOT SHA TSS. The response letter, timing, and phasing data have been attached to this Detailed Crash Investigation. margin-left:8px"> On Wednesday June 21, 2023, I received the Autopsy Report for Williamson. margin-left:8px">The Autopsy 23-03199 was performed by Dr. Theodore King Jr. Assistant Medical Director. The cause of death was listed as multiple injuries and the nature of death was accident. A review of the pathologic diagnoses the multiple injuries were the following: Abrasions, Contusions, and Subgaleal/ Subarachnoid hemorrhages.Lacerations of bilateral front cerebral peduncles of brain.Fractured odontoid pillar of C2 vertebra with fracture dislocation of odontoid joint C 1/C2 of base of skull with posterior displacement of odontoid pillar into spinal canal and crush injury of adjacent spinal cord (free floating head).Fracture dislocation of atlantooccipital joint (too wide), and C lIC2 cervical spinal column joint (too narrow) with posterior joint soft tissue hemorrhage and spinal cord contusion.Fracture/dislocation ofT4/T5 thoracic spinal column joint with epidural, subdural and subarachnoid hemorrhage of corresponding spinal cord with transection ofT4/T5 spinal cord. Dr. King opined that Betty Anne Williamson died of multiple injuries reportedly sustained as a driver involved in a collision with another motor vehicle. The manner of death is Accident. A toxicology report completed showed negative tests for drugs and alcohol. Section VII. - Analysis of Electronic Control Modules: See Sgt. Gore supplement report Section VIII. - Speed Analysis: No Speed Analysis was done on scene. However, the dash cam footage from Torres freightliner shows him traveling 56 mph at the time of impact. Section IX. - Crash Dynamics: The Crash Dynamics were determined by on scene evidence and confirmed by the dash camera footage supplied by Julian Torres Freightliner Truck. The Freightliner Truck pulling the Hub Group semi-trailer, operated by Julian Torres, was traveling southbound on Maryland Route 313approaching the Preston Road intersection. Torres had the green signal from the traffic control device and was attempting to continue south through the intersection. The white Ford Fusion, being operated by Betty Anne Williamson, was traveling east on Preston Rd (Rt. 318) and was stopped at the red signal prior to the intersection. As Torres was approaching the intersection in the Freightliner truck, Williamson disregarded the red signal and accelerated into the intersection. The Freightliner truck struck the driver side to the Ford Fusion. As a result of the collision, the Ford Fusion was redirected to a Southeast direction. The Fusion continued southeast until it came to a rest approximately 25 feet off the roadway in a grassy area. The Freightliner came to a position of controlled final rest just south of the intersection in the northbound lanes of Maryland Route 313. Section X. - Attachments that were included in for this report: The following items were attached to this report: margin-left:8px"> ACRS margin-left:8px"> Autopsy Report margin-left:8px"> Maryland Motor Carrier Safety Driver/Vehicle Examination Report margin-left:8px"> MDOT SHA Letter and Phasing Information margin-left:8px"> 72 Digital Photographs and uploaded to VeriPic. Conclusion: On March 10, 2023, at approximately 1430 hours, the Federalsburg Police Department responded to the intersection of Rt. 313 and Rt. 318 located in Federalsburg, Caroline County, Maryland for a two-vehicle motor vehicle collision involving a commercial vehicle tractor-trailer and a passenger car. The Freightliner Truck being operated by Julian Torres was traveling southbound on Route 313 approaching the Maryland route 318 intersection with a green signal from the traffic control device. Betty Anne Williamson operating a Ford Fusion was stopped at the steady red signal on Route 318 traveling eastbound. Just prior to Torres crossing the intersection, Williamson disregarded the red traffic signal and accelerated into the intersection. The Freightliner truck tractor struck the center of the Ford Fusion causing the vehicle to make a clockwise rotation from east to south. The impact sent the Ford Fusion off the roadway into the grass area on Route 313. Caroline EMS Paramedic 11 had pronounced Williamson deceased on scene at 1438 hours, run number 8636. These collision events were captured on Torres dash camera footage. This case is closed due to the death of at-fault party. All events occurred in Caroline County, MD.
